<p class=3D"eplus-wrapper">The four important parts of any division problem=
 are:</p>



<ul class=3D"eplus-wrapper wp-block-list">
<li class=3D"eplus-wrapper">Dividend</li>



<li class=3D"eplus-wrapper">Divisor</li>



<li class=3D"eplus-wrapper">Quotient</li>



<li class=3D"eplus-wrapper">Remainder</li>
</ul>



<p class=3D"eplus-wrapper">In a division problem, the number that is being =
divided is called dividend. The number that divides the dividend is called =
divisor. The result of the division is called a =E2=80=9Cquotient.=E2=80=9D=
 When the dividend is not completely divided by the divisor, the leftover v=
alue is called =E2=80=9Cremainder.=E2=80=9D</p>



<p class=3D"eplus-wrapper"><strong>Example: Divide 25 by 6.&nbsp;</strong><=
/p>



<p class=3D"eplus-wrapper">We know that <mjx-container class=3D"MathJax Ctx=
tMenu_Attached_0" jax=3D"CHTML" tabindex=3D"0" ctxtmenu_counter=3D"0" style=
